description._content: Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Miss Dulcie Stainton. Who wore a beautiful early 19th century period gown to represent Miss Single, a daughter of a pioneer wheat-grower. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Miss Mary Wentworth. Representing her great-grandmother, Mrs. William Wentworth, 1837. Miss Wentworth was president of the younger set committee. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Mr. K. Darby. Who made a handsome figure in the elegant costume of the period in his representation of John Edwards Eyre, the explorer. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Miss Helen Taylor. Who appeared as her great-great-grandmother, Mrs. Bunker, the wife of Captain Bunker, 1791. Miss Taylor danced in the minuet Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Mrs. Wentworth Grayson. Who organised the riding party at the pageant. She wore a costume, 1800 period, similar to that worn in the days of her great-grandmother, Mrs. John Single Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The Historical Pageant at Vaucluse House. Miss Uther Barker. A granddaughter of Reuben Uther, residing in the colony in 1897. Miss Barker represented her great-aunt Miss Ada Uther. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/607.
